About
Explore how sex has evolved throughout history at this museum with its extensive collection of explicit paintings, pictures, recordings, and artifacts. The exhibits detail over 100 years’ worth of sensual love from all the cultures of the world. Some pieces will make you laugh, while others are more thought-provoking. The museum, which opened in 1985, is the oldest of its kind still in operation. It’s located at the Damrak waterfront, one of the most vibrant areas in downtown Amsterdam. When you’re done touring the exhibits, grab a beer or a snack, or enjoy a canal cruise. – Tripadvisor
Duration: 1-2 hours

    Shady sex experience
    Visited this as part of our Amsterdam trip in February. Obviously we all know the story with Amsterdam and its links to the sex industry, drugs and whatever craziness it presents so therefore this was a must visit for us. The museum itself has this sort of “shadiness” feeling about it as you enter, being met by some smartly dressed hosts. When you enter you’re immediately met by various statues, images and a couple of electronic animations of a man being relieved in a toilet and also another man who opens his coat and surprises you. I think the whole point of the museum is to introduce you to the world of sex, the history behind it etc yet i felt this was just full of pornographic images from the 1910s all the way through to current day and also a small exhibition on historic condoms and other contraception. For the entry of ten euros per person it isn’t the worst, but when it’s done i don’t think i would make it a priority to return.
